<section class="story" id="story">
  <div class="story-grid">
    <div class="story-photo reveal" style="background-image:url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1502920917128-1aa500764cbd?auto=format&fit=crop&w=900&q=80');"></div>
    <div class="story-text reveal">
      <div class="eyebrow">Our Story</div>
      <h2 style="font-size:clamp(1.9rem,3.6vw,2.6rem); font-weight:400; margin:18px 0 22px; color:var(--ink); font-family:'Fraunces',serif;">Built from the place itself</h2>
      <p>Regiora began with one person who left the place they called home in search of new opportunities but never wanted to lose the memories of where they came from. As the years passed, photographs preserved what home looked like, but they could never recreate how it truly felt.</p>

      <p>The scent of the forests after rain, the breeze from the coastline, the warmth of the afternoon sun, and the atmosphere of familiar streets slowly faded with time. That inspired a simple idea: if a photograph could capture what a place looked like, perhaps the raw materials of that place could capture what it felt like — not a note that merely resembles cedar or citrus, but the cedar and citrus themselves, sourced from the ground they grew from.</p>

      <p>That idea became Regiora. Every fragrance is built from notes gathered directly from a real destination — its landscapes, climate, and culture, sourced rather than simulated. Each bottle is designed to help people reconnect with the places that shaped them, relive meaningful memories, and carry a genuine piece of home — or any unforgettable destination — wherever life takes them.</p>
